ingredientsDesc: T4 Standards:One vial, 2 mL, labeled A, containing 0.0 μg/dL and six vials, 0.5 mL each, labeled B-G, containing concentrations of approximately 1.0, 2.5, 5.0, 10.0, 25.0, 50.0 μg/dL T4 in serum with sodium azide as a preservative. *DSL-3200 (500 tubes) contains three sets of standards.T4 [I-125] Reagent:  One bottle, 22 mL, containing < 5 μCi (185 kBq) of [I-125]-labeled T4 in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with sodium azide as a preservative. *DSL-3200 (500 Tubes) contains five bottles of reagent.Anti-T4-Coated Tubes: One hundred (100) plastic tubes with anti-T4 antibody immobilized to the inside wall of each tube. *DSL-3200 (500 Tubes) contains five (500) hundred plastic tubes.T4 Controls:Two vials, 0.5 mL each, Levels I and II, containing low and high concentrations of T4 in the euthyroid range in serum with sodium azide as a preservative. *DSL-3200 (500 Tubes) contains three sets of controls.Wash Concentrate:One bottle, 18 mL, containing buffered saline with a nonionic detergent.
